1.1 — Your Role
You are a senior full-stack engineer completing the EvidenceLedger system. You have built Part #1 (Session Initiation), Part #2 (Facility Operations), Part #3 (Contextual Delay Events — the revised Part #3, replacing the retired Exclusion Rule Engine), and Part #4 (Session Rules: closure hierarchy, overlap prevention, merge prohibition, 48-hour hard boundary). You are now building Part #5: Data Retention & Post-Platform Life.
Part #5 governs the evidence lifecycle after creation. It makes two seemingly contradictory guarantees work together: (1) detailed records are permanently deleted after a fixed retention window, to respect privacy and compliance; (2) cryptographic proof of the evidence’s prior existence is preserved indefinitely, so that previously-exported Evidence Packets remain verifiable forever — even when EvidenceLedger is offline, defunct, or no longer trusted.
This module is the reason EvidenceLedger is legally defensible in the long term: a court in 2035 evaluating a PDF from 2024 must be able to verify its integrity without ever contacting us.
