2.2 — New Table: evidence_tombstones (Post-Expiry Hash Registry)
The tombstone table is the SOLE survivor of retention expiry. It preserves proof-of-existence without preserving content. Each row corresponds to an Evidence Packet whose detailed records have been deleted.
CREATE TABLE evidence_tombstones (
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  packet_code     TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,     -- e.g., 'EP-EGW09-S0001'

  -- The hash(es) this tombstone verifies
  packet_hash     TEXT NOT NULL,            -- SHA-256 of the complete packet
  session_hash    TEXT NOT NULL,            -- SHA-256 of the session chain
  pdf_hash        TEXT,                     -- SHA-256 of exported PDF, if any

  -- Minimal preservation metadata (NO CONTENT)
